## 6. Summary for Creating a New Channel Plugin

To create a new channel plugin, replicate this minimal structure:

```
extensions/my-channel/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          (manifest with id, channels, configSchema)
├── package.json                  (with openclaw config block)
├── index.ts                      (defineChannelPluginEntry)
├── setup-entry.ts                (defineSetupPluginEntry)
├── api.ts                        (public API barrel)
├── runtime-api.ts                (runtime barrel)
└── src/
    ├── channel.ts                (main plugin def)
    ├── runtime.ts                (runtime store)
    ├── accounts.ts               (account management)
    ├── config-schema.ts          (config schema)
    ├── setup-core.ts             (setup logic)
    ├── setup-surface.ts          (UI)
    ├── probe.ts                  (validation)
    ├── send.ts                   (outbound messages)
    ├── monitor.ts                (inbound events)
    └── types.ts                  (type definitions)
```

The pattern is consistent: define the channel plugin using `createChatChannelPlugin()` from the SDK, export it from index.ts, and implement the required methods for sending, monitoring, and setup.

